Oak Street, north side, east from but not including Roosevelt, to and including James Streets. Nos. 22-26 Oak Street, east of the N.E. corner of Roosevelt Street, are frame houses with brick fronts.

1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.

(1) Roosevelt Street, (not shown), west side, between Oak and Cherry Streets, showing the rears of buildings facing on Oak Street. The white building in the center background, is the rear of the 5th Precinct Police Station, as seen from the former site of P.S. No. 112. In the left background, is the tower of the Municipal Building, and on the right, the tower of the Federal Courts Building, before completion.

April 25, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.
